		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I ran across this article via hackaday:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.ppl-pilot.com/index.htm">http://www.ppl-pilot.com/index.htm</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />It describes how to create wireless SNES/NES controllers for use with the Gamecube ports on the Wii. 
<br />
<br />I'm assuming that with a few changes, these could work on original machines too. The article mentions a materials cost of about $80 US per controller and receiver.  Although I'm fairly confident I could assemble one myself, I'd gladly pay $150 for someone else to make me a set. Any takers?
<br />
<br />I know they already make infrared stuff for the NES but I think these would work waaaaaay better.

		

